>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Combining all 8 focus items...</span><hr size=1> Since Verant's looking into pets right now, let's hope they make some good changes for us all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We've heard a lot of people talk about the usefulness of the pet focus items: the four from Solusek Ro and the Staves of Mastery. The former enhances HP/Stats of pet while the latter enhances Level alone.<br>
<br>
Why not introduce a single item which combines the effects of all eight items? AN item which not onyl boosts the pet's level but also their statistics aswell? The cumulative increase would hopefully be noticable...<br>
<br>
However, this item woudl be very rare due to the cumulative rareness of the staves and rarely (if ever) anyone is in posession of all four.<br>
<br>
Also, why do the Solusek Ro items cap at Level 49? Wouldn't it make sense for them to scale to 60? Level is preferable to stat boosts so it would not subtract from the usefulness of the staves. &lt;also you can onyl use one at a time&gt;<br>
<br>
How about puting an NPC into the Temple of Solusek Ro who does not communicate with players under 44. With this NPC, you can hand in all four focus items from the lower quests and recieve a single item which is a combination of the four:<br>
<br>
EG.<br>
<br>
Staff of Elemental Flux<br>
Slot: Primary<br>
Dmg 6<br>
Del 25<br>
Int +8, Str +3, Agi +3, Save v. Cold +5, Save v. Heat +5.<br>
Effect: Reclaim Energy<br>
WT 0.1<br>
<br>
This item will have the focus effect on all pets cast up to 60. If it needs to be made more costly, then add a monetary cost to the quest too. Perhapse a few K? Money is rarely an issue for Magicians who can easily kill a Hill Giant solo. Or do something along the lines of the Wizard Staff of the Wheel and have a separate section for the container quest &lt;okay, for wizzies you only have to ask for it&gt; which would cost the characters a fair bit of money.<br>
<br>
This is also quite a nice item to have equipped in your primary slot! You may have something better depending on your success with your character but I would probably prefer to have this perma-equipped along with my Moggok Stein. The stats have a marginal advantage over the wizard staff of the wheel and that quest is even more simple (even if the melee statistics are pitiful), but if the item would need to be made less powerful, why not just take away the melee attributes all together? As if we would notice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It would also save us a bit of inventory weight and space. &lt;I hardly ever put items of this importance into summoned containers! LD is so fearful!&gt;<br>
<br>
If anyone has any helpful comments and criticisms, please post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Or alternative ideas would be good too!<br>
<br>
This isn't a groundbreakign change, but it's still one I'd like to see. Maybe even duplicate the quest for the staves of mastery too and combine the two resulting staves to create a greater effect. Maybe add 5 levels to the pet and boost all stats by around 15-30%? Hey, if you don't suggest ideas, nothing happens <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#333333>(5/16/02 3:24:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  I like it..</span><hr size=1> I'd make the staff stats ALOT better. I'd also put stats on the current Mastery Staves. <br>
<br>
As for why the current 34 focus items don't work on 49+, at the time verant(kunark release) found pets to be over powering, and decided to cap them at lvl 49. In some ways, the 34 focus items are actually much more potent than the 50+ ones. Like the HP bonuses for example.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(5/16/02 1:47:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Really???</span><hr size=1> Really???<br>
<br>
I thought the heightened level would give the pet much more damage output/mitigation potential than simple statistic increases...<br>
<br>
And it has come to Verant's relaisation that pets are not overpowered post 50+ (or they wouldnt' have improved them) so let's see if they take the 49 cap off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For a Level 50 wizard who has the Staff of Elemental Mastery: Water and the Stein of Ulissia, which one would he/she use??<br>
<br>
If it's the case the the Sol Ro. items are preferable, the shouldn't the staves have their effect increased?<br>
<br>
I'd fully support making the stats on the staff of elemental flux (my made up item) more powerful, but I was suggesting a much more simple quest item. The quest would need to be made much harder for better stats. The only reason I suggested it was to save us Mages some space (plus the cumulative effects are nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(5/16/02 7:01:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Details...</span><hr size=1> Okay, since I want to avoid writing my university essay, I'll give a more detailed outline of the fixes I'd like to see to the focus items...<br>
<br>
1 - Remove the Level 49 cap on the Solusek Ro items.<br>
<br>
2 - Impliment a quest for the 44+ Magician market to combine all 4 Solusek Ro foci into the above weapon. EG: NPC in Sol Ro gives you a box with 4 spaces. You must get it imbued by 4 other wandering Magicians (Akistaff in Najena and Walna in BBM could be 2). All these mages require a monetary fee since platinum dust is needed as the spell component. Say 200pp per person. Then you put your 4 foci into the container and hit combine. You recieve the message &quot;You lacked the skill to create somethign new&quot;, freak out and realise an item on your cursor. It identifies as &quot;Mangled elements&quot;. You then hand this back to the Sol Ro NPC and he/she fashions the mess into the Staff of Elemental Flux (my madeup item) for another fee of maybe 500pp. &lt;hey, why can't I have fun quests??&gt;<br>
<br>
3 - Up the level effect of the Elemental Mastery Staves and impliment above quest for the staves too!<br>
<br>
4 - Allow both quest pieces to be combined into the uber-foci for Magicians! And give the Orb of Mastery the same effect <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uodibillauxes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odibil Lauxes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(5/17/02 1:02:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Details...</span><hr size=1> I'll agree with number four.<br>
<br>
I also believe the Orb of Mastery should possess the same focus modifiers as the four elemental staves combined.<br>
<br>
I base this on the fact that nobody in their right mind would possess any focus item aside from the fire staff, unless they were quite greedy, or very fortunate.<br>
<br>
The quest involved for the air staff is ridiculous, as the crown required is used as a part of our epic, which is not a walk in the park to obtain. Both the earth and water staves are also used as a part of our epic, and very rarely will anyone possess a second staff that is not going to be multiquested away at one point, unless they are privileged enough to do so.<br>
<br>
So in essence, you're giving up all of your focus items to concentrate the power into the Orb of Mastery, and all attributes of those focus items should still remain in the orb. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=201.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=201.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=201.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=201.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=201.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administra